## Local Development (All Free, Self-Hosted)

```bash
# Start the minimal free stack (API + MLflow + Redis)
docker-compose up samos-api mlflow-server redis-cache

# Start with monitoring too
docker-compose up

# Start with NiFi enterprise data ingestion (optional)
docker-compose --profile enterprise up nifi

# View your services
open http://localhost:7860   # SAMOS API + Dashboard
open http://localhost:5000   # MLflow Tracking
open http://localhost:3000   # Grafana (admin/changeme)
open http://localhost:9090   # Prometheus
```

---

## What You DO NOT Need to Pay For

| Service | Why It's Not Needed |
|---|---|
| **AWS / GCP / Azure** | HF Spaces runs the API for free |
| **Render.com paid** | HF Spaces free tier doesn't spin down for public spaces |
| **Railway.app** | Docker Compose runs everything locally |
| **Datadog / New Relic** | Prometheus + Grafana (self-hosted, free) handles monitoring |
| **GitHub Copilot** | Not needed for this project |
| **SonarQube Enterprise** | SonarCloud free tier covers public repos |

---

## Summary: Activation Order

```bash
# 1. Make repo public on GitHub

# 2. Delete dead CI stubs + push (CI auto-starts)
git rm .github/workflows/*.disabled
git add .github/workflows/
git commit -m "ci: activate free CI/CD"
git push

# 3. Create HF Space (Docker SDK, public)
# 4. Add HF_TOKEN + HF_SPACE_ID to GitHub Secrets
# 5. Sign up for DagsHub, SonarCloud, Codecov (all free, all GitHub login)
# 6. Add their tokens to GitHub Secrets

# 7. Push to main — CI runs + HF Space auto-deploys
git commit --allow-empty -m "🚀 First deploy"
git push origin main
```

Done. Fully operational. Fully free.
